## Description {#details}

An itinerary represents the scheduling information for an instruction.

This includes a set of stages occupied by the instruction and the pipeline cycle in which operands are read and written.

Definition at line 99 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/mc/mcinstritineraries-h">MCInstrItineraries.h</a>.
